title: For Sale:  Remington Model 11
postcontent:
This old M11 has been very well loved. It has an even brown patina on the metal, but very little pitting or actual crusty rust. All of the metal has been meticulously cleaned with flitz polish, and well oiled. The finish is actually nice looking, and in no way impacts the function of the firearm.
Speaking of the action, these M11's are the American-Made equivalent of the Browning A5. This means it is a long-recoil action. The barrel cycles backwards with the bolt for the full length of the cartridge before releasing. This makes for a very unique recoil impulse, and a quite reliable autoloading shotgun! The mechanism can be adjusted for different loads, and will cycle nearly anything if set up properly.If you are looking for a very unique shotgun with a mechanism that is different from anything else, look no further!
